      • obtainWhereInWithClause

        private static java.lang.StringBuilder obtainWhereInWithClause(CypRel cR,
                                                               MatchClause matchC,
                                                               java.lang.StringBuilder sql,
                                                               boolean isBiDirectional,
                                                               int indexRel,
                                                               java.lang.String nodeLabel1,
                                                               java.lang.String nodeLabel2)
        Augmenting the WITH clauses with the correct predicates (that may be associated with either the nodes or properties of the relationship itself).
        Parameters:
        cR - The Cypher relationship: (a)-[b]->(c) for example.
        matchC - The MatchClause: MATCH (a)-[b]->(c) ...
        sql - The current SQL being created.
        isBiDirectional - If the relationship has no direction (i.e. -[]- as opposed to <-[] and -[]->), then need to append UNION ALL to the end of the SQL created.
        indexRel - The position of the relationship within the context of the whole MatchClause.
        nodeLabel1 - Label(s) of the left node of the relationship.
        nodeLabel2 - Label(s) of the right node of the relationship.
        Returns:
        SQL string with additional information as a result of this method.
